title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant 91/30 Sniper Rifle
postcontent: 1944 Izhevsk Mosin Nagant Sniper Rifle with clear scope and scope covers and bent sniper bolt. All original. This version was given to Yugoslavia by Russia after WWII and then used as police sniper rifles before the scopes were removed and they were sold. They have a unique feature in that the head of the cleaning rod was "brazed" on. The numbers are not matching between the parts as were most of these that were given to Yugoslavia. Bright crisp bore and the stock is in the original wood without any shelac or other coating (shelac and grease was applied to Mosins for storage purposes).
